{{Sangam literature}}
'''Paranar''' ([[Tamil language|Tamil]]: பரணர்) (c. 1st century CE) was a poet of the [[Sangam period]], to whom 84 verses of the Sangam literature have been attributed, besides verse 6 of the [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref>{{cite book | last = Vedanayagam | first = Rama | author-link = | title =Tiruvalluva Maalai: Moolamum Eliya Urai Vilakkamum | publisher = Manimekalai Prasuram | series = | volume = | edition = 1 | date = 2017 | location = Chennai | pages =17 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
==Biography== Paranar belonged to the Paanar caste. He was the friend of [[Kapilar]]<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/> and [[Nakkirar I]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = Agananuru, Purananuru | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 3 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 243 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref> He has sung various kings, namely, Kadal Pirakkottiya Senguttuvan, Cholan Uruvapatrer Ilanchet Senni, Cheraman Kadalottiya Velkelu Kuttuvan, Kudakko Neduncheralaadhan, and Cholan Verpatradakkai Perunarkilli.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_3"/>
==Contribution to the Sangam literature== Paranar has written about 85 verses, including 17 in [[Kurunthogai]], 12 in [[Natrinai]], 32 in [[Agananuru]], 13 in [[Purananuru]], 10 in [[Pathitrupathu]], and 1 in [[Tiruvalluva Maalai]].<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2">{{cite book | last = Kowmareeshwari (Ed.) | first = S. | author-link = | title = Kurunthogai, Paripaadal, Kalitthogai | publisher = Saradha Pathippagam | series = Sanga Ilakkiyam | volume = 2 | edition = 1 | date = August 2012 | location = Chennai | pages = 442 | language = Tamil | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = | mr = | zbl = | jfm = }}</ref>
By praising the Chera king Senguttuvan, Paranar received Udambarkaattu Vaari and his son prince Kuttuvan Cheral as 'present'.<ref name="SangaIlakkiyam_2"/>
